In .NET 10, Android's `adjustResize` behavior changed because MAUI now defaults to **edge-to-edge** rendering (required on Android 15+). The window no longer physically resizes; instead you must react to **keyboard insets**.

## Recommended fix

**1. Keep `adjustResize` in `AndroidManifest.xml`:**
```xml
<activity ... android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize" />
```

**2. Apply keyboard inset padding via a platform handler on your page/view:**

```csharp
// In MauiProgram.cs or a handler customization
#if ANDROID
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;
#endif

// On your root layout (e.g., a Grid), add a handler:
Microsoft.Maui.Handlers.LayoutHandler.Mapper.AppendToMapping("KeyboardInsets", (handler, view) =>
{
#if ANDROID
    var platformView = handler.PlatformView;
    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(platformView, new KeyboardInsetsListener(view));
#endif
});
```

**3. Create the insets listener (Android only):**

```csharp
#if ANDROID
using AndroidX.Core.Graphics;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    private readonly ILayout _layout;

    public KeyboardInsetsListener(ILayout layout) => _layout = layout;

    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Use the larger of IME or nav bar bottom inset
        int bottomPx = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
        double bottomDp = bottomPx / v.Context.Resources.DisplayMetrics.Density;

        // Apply as padding to the MAUI layout
        ((Microsoft.Maui.IView)_layout).Margin = new Thickness(0, 0, 0, bottomDp);

        return insets;
    }
}
#endif
```

## Simpler alternative — ScrollView + built-in auto-scroll

If your chat input is inside a `ScrollView`, MAUI's built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` may handle it automatically. Ensure it's enabled (it's on by default):

```csharp
// To re-enable if you previously disabled it:
KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect();
```

## TL;DR

| .NET 9 | .NET 10 |
|--------|---------|
| `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` | Listen to `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` and adjust padding/margin |

The insets approach is future-proof and works with edge-to-edge on all Android versions.
